Clone GB8-46 contained a base deletion between residues 5935 and 5937. This was repaired with a G insertion at position 5936 to generate the infectious molecular clone GB8-46R

The vpu reading frame is disrupted due to deletion of 9 base pairs encompassing the ATG start (between positions 6080/81 of GB8-46R, equivalent to bases 6062-6070 of HXB2) and a 2 base pair insertion (GB8-46R 6186/7 corresponding to an insertion between bases 6175/6 of HXB2). The latter causes a reading frame shift and premature truncation of the protein (the true stop codon resides at positions 6317-9 in GB8-46R and 6308-6310 in HXB2).
